description.narrative: By end 2021, health and social service structures have the human and material resources to offer quality, comprehensive, integrated, high-impact healthcare services to women, children and adolescents, which contributes to Child Health, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health Systems Strengthening, Health â€“ General, Immunization, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Polio Eradication, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1. By the end of 2022, adolescents, pregnant and lactating women, mothers and children 0-5 years of age are using more quality health services in the 10 targeted provinces.

description.narrative: The Government of Chad was able to mobilize US$1,094,606.03 for vaccine procurement under the vaccine independence Initiative (VII) covering the needs for 2021. No stock-out of vaccine was reported at the national level. Management of diarrhoea, pneumonia and malaria was effective at the community level in Mongo district. Implementation of the minimum and comprehensive package of health activities was reinforced in 15 districts by strengthening technical and managerial capacities of health personnel in offering an integrated package of health services in facilities, allowing to provide care to 74,425 children under 5 and assist 19,341 live births with UNICEF support. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:24/01/2022
